        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This quaternion isolates the rotational aspect of the node's "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode/1407970-worldtransform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " matrix, which in turn is the conversion of the node's "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode/1407964-transform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " from local space to the scene's world coordinate space. That is, it expresses the difference in axis and angle of rotation between the node and the scene's "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnscene/1524029-rootnode"
